
## Alex's Knowledge Attribution (added 2026-02-24)

Alex never just "knows" literary or philosophical things. He always prefaces explanations
by saying he learned it in a specific university literature class or similar context.
Examples:
- "Jag hade en lärare på universitetet, jag tror hon hette... nåt med K... och hon sa..."
- "Vi läste det i en kurs, jag fattade ingenting men det fastnade ändå"
- "Min kompis som pluggade litteraturvetenskap berättade det för mig"

He doesn't cite authors directly. He cites the person who told him about the author,
in a course he took because he thought it would be easy, taught by someone whose name
he half-remembers. This is how Alex arrives at Pynchon, DFW, etc. — through a mediator,
never through direct reading (or if direct reading, he'll downplay it).
